label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, mononucleate cell with elongated germ tube

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an elongated germ tube, and in which the nucleus does not divide. The cell does not divide, and eventually dies.

label.value: activation of monopolar cell growth at new end

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the activation of monopolar cell growth occurs at the new end of the cell, instead of at the old end, following cell division.

label.value: actin cables absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cell does not contain detectable actin cables.

label.value: normal protein localization to growing cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the growing cell tip is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to growing cell tip, with protein distributed in plasma membrane or cortex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a growing cell tip is decreased, and the protein is also detected distributed throughout the plasma membrane and/or cell cortex.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished galactose-specific flocculation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell adhesion phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which galactose-specific flocculation does not occur. Galactose-specific flocculation is the non-sexual aggregation of cells, mediated via the binding of cell wall proteins on one cell to galactose residues on the other.

label.value: increased mannose-specific flocculation

value.value: A cell adhesion phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mannose-specific flocculation is increased. Mannose-specific flocculation is the non-sexual aggregation of cells, mediated via the binding of cell wall proteins on one cell to mannose residues on the other, and when it is increased cells adhere to each other more strongly or to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: abnormal NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity is abnormal.

definition.value: Also consider using the cellular process phenotype term 'abnormal cellular respiration' (FYPO:0000078).

label.value: decreased NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity is decreased.

definition.value: Also consider using the cellular process phenotype term 'decreased cellular respiration' (FYPO:0000342).

label.value: abnormal succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity is abnormal.

definition.value: Also consider using the cellular process phenotype term 'abnormal cellular respiration' (FYPO:0000078).

label.value: abolished succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which succinate dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) activity is absent.

definition.value: Also consider using the cellular process phenotype term 'decreased cellular respiration' (FYPO:0000342).

label.value: altered cytochrome absorption spectrum

value.value: A phenotype in which the spectrum of light absorption observed in whole cells or isolated mitochondria, and attributed to cytochromes present, differs from wild type.

label.value: resistance to methotrexate

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of methotrexate than normal.

label.value: normal interphase microtubule nucleation

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleation of microtubules is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Normally, microtubules are nucleated from interphase microtubule organizing centers (iMTOCs) and from the cytoplasmic face of the spindle pole body (SPB).

label.value: curved interphase microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form cytoplasmic microtubules that are curved, i.e. follow a smooth bend rather than a straight line, during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: misoriented interphase microtubules

value.value: A microtubule organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the orientation of cytoplasmic microtubules within a cell is abnormal during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. The normal orientation is parallel to the long axis of the cell.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cell tip during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell tip does not occur during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to new mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the new mitotic spindle pole body is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein kinase activity during mitotic interphase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein kinase activity is decreased during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: normal protein kinase activity during mitotic interphase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein kinase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: inviable lemon-shaped cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a single cell is inviable, and grows in the form of a lemon prior to cell death. A lemon shape is defined mathematically as having a quadric surface in three dimensions obtained by rotating less than half of a circular arc about an axis passing through the endpoints of the arc.

label.value: normal protein localization to septin ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the septin ring is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased galactose-specific flocculation

value.value: A cell population phenotype that reflects increased occurrence of galactose-specific flocculation. Galactose-specific flocculation is the non-sexual aggregation of single cells, mediated by the binding of cell wall proteins on one cell to galactose residues on the other.

label.value: increased duration of protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or more proteins is localized to the actomyosin contractile ring for a longer time than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to septum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell septum is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal actomyosin contractile ring morphology

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of the actomyosin contractile ring is abnormal.

label.value: decreased rate of actomyosin contractile ring assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actomyosin contractile ring assembly is decreased. Contractile ring assembly is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring is formed of actin, myosin, and associated proteins.

label.value: decreased re-entry into mitotic cell cycle during recovery from stationary phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of re-entry into the mitotic cell cycle is decreased when the cell is in a population that has been in stationary phase and is then placed in conditions that allow recovery.

label.value: multinucleate

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which a cell contains more than one nucleus.

label.value: elongated multinucleate cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell contains more than one nucleus, is longer than normal, and has a greater length:diameter ratio than normal.

label.value: elongated multinucleate multiseptate cell, single septa between nuclei

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is elongated, has two or more nuclei and more than one septum, and the septa not grouped together, but are located so as to form separate compartments with a single nucleus in each.

label.value: elongated multinucleate multiseptate cell, single septa between nuclei, during stationary phase

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed when a cell population is in stationary phase in which a cell is elongated, has two or more nuclei and more than one septum, and the septa not grouped together, but are located so as to form separate compartments with a single nucleus in each.

label.value: abolished cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase in response to nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of cell cycle arrest in response to nitrogen starvation does not occur; arrest normally occurs in G1 phase.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0.

label.value: abnormal meiotic recombination at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which reciprocal meiotic recombination is abnormal at the silent mating-type cassettes. Meiotic recombination is a cellular process in which double strand breaks are formed and repaired through a double Holliday junction intermediate, resulting in the equal exchange of genetic material between non-sister chromatids in a pair of homologous chromosomes.

label.value: altered substrate specificity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the substrate specificity of a catalytic activity differs from wild type.

label.value: altered substrate specificity, glutathione synthetase to homoglutathione synthetase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the substrate specificity of a gene product that executes glutathione synthetase activity in wild type is altered such that the gene product executes homoglutathione synthetase activity.

label.value: normal protein localization to mitotic spindle midzone during anaphase B

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle midzone during anaphase B is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The mitotic spindle midzone is the area in the center of the mitotic spindle where the spindle microtubules from opposite poles overlap. Anaphase B is the stage of mitosis in which the polar microtubules elongate and the two poles of the spindle move farther apart.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to mitotic spindle midzone during anaphase B

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle midzone during anaphase B does not occur. The mitotic spindle midzone is the area in the center of the mitotic spindle where the spindle microtubules from opposite poles overlap. Anaphase B is the stage of mitosis in which the polar microtubules elongate and the two poles of the spindle move farther apart.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased duration of protein localization to kinetochore during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or more proteins is localized to the kinetochore of a chromosome for a longer time than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased DNA double-strand break formation at mating-type locus

value.value: A DNA recombination phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which DNA double-strand break formation occurs to a lower extent than normal during gene conversion at the mating-type locus.

label.value: normal DNA double-strand break formation at mating-type locus

value.value: A DNA recombination phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which DNA double-strand break formation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during gene conversion at the mating-type locus.

label.value: decreased galactose level in glycoprotein glycan

value.value: A phenotype in which the glycan moiety of a glycoprotein contains a lower amount of galactose residues than normal. In wild-type cells, glycoprotein glycans contain mannose and galactose residues in a 1:1.2 ratio, and the galactose residues are connected by alpha-1,2 linkages.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for sulfur-containing amino acid

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize sulfur-containing amino acids, and therefore requires one or more sulfur-containing amino acids (e.g. cysteine or methionine) in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: sensitive to papuamide B during mating

value.value: A phenotype in which cells show increased sensitivity to papuamide B during mating. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of papuamide B that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to filipin

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to filipin. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of filipin that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to miconazole

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to miconazole. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of miconazole that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to myriocin during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to myriocin. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of myriocin that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: abolished superoxide dismutase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which superoxide dismutase activity is absent.

label.value: normal superoxide dismutase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of superoxide dismutase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal protein acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein acetylation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Protein acetylation is the addition of an acetyl group to a protein amino acid.
